t="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Frank Thorp V</media:credit><media:text type="plain">“There’s some things I wish were better,” Bacon said. “But am I going to vote to raise taxes on middle-class Americans? I’m not.”</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-02/260213-John-Cavanaugh-ew-212p-021dea.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Wroblewski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Nebraska Democratic State Senator John Cavanaugh</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-denise-powell-for-congress-vl-346p-2d55d2.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1366" width="2048"><media:credit>Denise Powell for Congress</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Denise Powell stands inside of a room smiling with her arms cross</media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260511-cindy-burbank-william-forbes-nebraska-mb-1126-25b126.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="800" width="1200"><media:credit>cindyburbank.com; forbesfornebraska</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Cindy Burbank and William Forbes are facing off in Nebraska&#39;s Democratic Senate primary. </media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2024-01/240130-Shelley-Moore-Capito-se-1129a-59c2ff.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Drew Angerer</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Sen. Shelley Moore Capito, R-W.V., speaks during a news conference </media:text><media:description type="plain">Retiring Republican Rep. Don Bacon&#39;s Nebraska district will be a key battleground for both parties in the fight for the House majority. </media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2025-07/250703-don-bacon-se-428p-e78b66.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:42 GMT</pubDate><title>Tuesday’s primaries to set up key fall matchups in Nebraska</title><updateDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 09:00:42 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Jane Lytvynenko</dc:creator><dc:creator>Stella Kim</dc:creator><dc:creator>Jared Perlo</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:00:27 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Kim So-young is accused of asking ChatGPT for lethal dosing advice before giving three men benzodiazepine-laced drinks. Two died.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/chatgpt-advised-south-korea-woman-3-men-poison-police-say-rcna344063</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/chatgpt-advised-south-korea-woman-3-men-poison-police-say-rcna344063</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260512-chat-gpt-south-korea-lr-460452.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1600" width="2400"><media:credit>Leila Register</media:credit><media:text type="plain">A criminal case riveting South Korea has echoes of cases involving AI that are popping up around the world.</media:text><media:description type="plain">A criminal case riveting South Korea has echoes of cases involving AI that are popping up around the world.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260512-chat-gpt-south-korea-lr-460452.jpg" height="1600" width="2400"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:00:27 GMT</pubDate><title>Authorities say she asked ChatGPT about mixing alcohol and meds. Then, two men turned up dead.</title><updateDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 16:00:27 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Yuliya Talmazan</dc:creator><dateTimeWritten>Tue, 12 May 2026 17:00:00 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>College students across Russia are being lured to join the country’s drone forces in Ukraine but rights activists say the offer could be a trap.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/russia/russia-recruit-students-drone-pilots-ukraine-putin-war-rcna331675</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/world/russia/russia-recruit-students-drone-pilots-ukraine-putin-war-rcna331675</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260415-russia-rs-36ec3c.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Getty Images</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Russia Daily Life 2026</media:text><media:description type="plain">A billboard in St. Petersburg, Russia, advertising a contract in Russia&#39;s drone forces. The sign reads: &#34;The new ones. The irreplaceable ones. Russian unmanned troops.&#34; </media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260512-russia-drone-mb-1256-46d00e.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Sergey Boby